^-|cp||cs||ht|e|fp||AT|^B@2^*BMM: ^*NIn other sections, with help from |CP|1|AT|^*GAK,The Panel^*N|CP||AT|, we reviewed the guidelines for what action to take after the RHO opens a suit. They are a pass, or an overcall, or a 1N bid, or make a takeout double. What is left is an attempt to learn the thought processes which experts use to make takeout doubles that "more often than not" give them good result—the small prints. Many items such as vulnerability, the position at the table, suit opened by the opponents and few others strongly influence experts in making a takeout double. There are agreements and of course there are differences. Before, we get to the list of small print let us have a short review of what we have learned. BTW, you can meet the panel by clicking the blue link above and then come back here.|
