NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*BHoward: ^*N|cp||at|And, very importantly, if it goes 4S-4N-P-5D-P-?, responder must be prepared for the 4N bidder to correct to 5H (if the 4N bidder had hearts and clubs). So responder to the 4N bidder must not bid 5H (rarely it would be ok with a self-sufficient suit) and should only bid 5D if they are prepared to hear a correction to 5H.|
